[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Takes the guesswork out of alchemy by showing what a combination will produce before you craft it, and patches a gap where researched recipes weren't actually registered as known.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Live preview on the alchemy stations[/b] — the mortar, alchemy workbench, and mixer now show what a given ingredient combination will produce, provided you've already researched or crafted it once. No more pulling up a wiki.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Research counts as "known"[/b] — vanilla used to require that you actually craft a recipe once before it showed up in the preview, even if you'd already researched all its ingredients. This mod registers every researched recipe as known so the preview works immediately.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Works across alchemy tiers[/b] — applies to the base alchemy bench and the higher-tier stations added by story progression.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3]Unlock path: the mod activates the moment you first interact with any alchemy station. Progression is entirely the game's normal tech tree — this mod doesn't add or gate any features behind perks.[/size]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/86]Decomp Delight[/url] — shows what element (Chaos, Life, etc.) each item decomposes into in the mill / mixer / distillation cube. Natural companion to Alchemy Research Redux.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue batches of alchemy crafts. QE's per-workbench auto-craft also covers the alchemy workbench.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory across workstations means alchemy ingredients are accessible from every bench.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — speed up alchemy crafting.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

